				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="1"><b>Everlore Site Downtime</b></a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:xanthus@everlore.com">Xanthus</b></a>
				[12/5/2000-4:53:15 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=292766"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[0]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
<p>
We have been in the process of moving our servers over to a new offsite host since last Friday. You may have noticed the site being much slower then usual since then. All of our sites will be down for about 1-2 hours at around 6:00PM PST today for the final move.</p>
<p>
After we have everything setup up offsite, we will be running off a ultra high speed line which can burst up to 100mbps of bandwidth.</p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="2">Evening news bites from Absor</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[12/5/2000-4:51:26 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=292819"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[0]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037454.html">If you are new to Velious, you need to run the Velious Patcher</a></B><P>

<I>If you are new to Velious you will need to run the Velious patch. After starting EverQuest the patcher will update your standard EverQuest files. Then at the bottom you will see several option buttons for updating specific parts of the game. If you have just installed Velious, you will need to choose to update Velious by clicking on that button.<P>

Thank you.<P>

Alan</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>



<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037094.html">Stacks of Bandages, Food, Water, etc.</a></B><P>

Wait and wait.... wait.... wait..... even after Abashi said it will de done soon. The implementation for a npc vendor to sell 20 food/water/bandages/arrows as a stack still not released even after many patches recently.<P>

<B>Soon is an interesting word…<P>

It is definitely something that we want to do. It's not, unfortunately, a trivial thing to do. It's on Rowyl's list. But when it gets done isn't something that I'm willing to predict right now.<P>

Keep in mind, though, that we play this game too, and we have to buy just as much food and water as you guys do.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037213.html">Rogues Cant drag corps anymore</a></B><P>

Demonspawn wrote: "1. You are added to the nearby mobs hate list. In this case hide/sneek won't mean diddly. You will be attacked. Invis means nothing to an agroed mob. <P>

2. Your faction is reduced to KOS with the nearby mobs. In this case, hide/sneek will work. However, are we sure that the faction hits will be temporary? Given Verant's track record, I think we are in for a mess. 
But no, I havn't read the updated online manual (I'm at work). I am basing this off of what Absor put in his posts."<P>

<B>Not based on what I posted.<P>

Invisibility and hide and all other such things will work just fine, even if you are dragging a corpse in a place where the new /corpse coding is in use. That is, dragging a corpse will not harm your invisibility or hiding.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037367.html">EQ's 300,000+ subscribers falling short</a></B><P>

<B>We really have no reason to lie about our numbers to you.</B><P>

Sinseraph wrote: "why do you keep painting a picture that EQ is great and loved by 300,000+ people when in reality half of those have cancelled those subscriptions since release? you say EQ is so great and full of good challenge, content, and expansions, then shouldn't those cancelled subscriptions have been anticipating teh next big release? the next big challenge as you so thrive on? huh, well where are they? they must be missing out eh?"<P>

<B>We do have over 300,000 active subscribers. That's true. We also believe that having that many subscribers does indicate that a lot of people are enjoying the game. The only place where your figures were correct (actually, a bit high) is when you calculated that about 76,000 people are playing EverQuest during peak hours. I think that's a pretty large number, and that alone indicates that EverQuest is a successful product.<P>

And, yes, we think that EverQuest is a great game full of good challenge, content and expansions.<P>

As for those that are anticipating the 'next big challenge'… I was just at an EB today that had sold their 120 copies of Scars of Velious in only a few hours.<P>

I had nothing to do with the building of the game. If I had, though, I would be extremely proud of that kind of response from the customers. I think the team has created a great product. I'm honored to be associated with it, even in this small way.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037421.html">Screenshots in Velious</a></B><P>

<I>As some of you may know, we disabled the ability to take screen shots during the testing of Velious.<P>

Unfortunately, we forgot to re-enable screen shots when the expansion went live. This means that those of you with Velious accounts can't take screen shots right now. We will turn them back on with the patch this Thursday.<P>

Sorry about that…<P>

Alan</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037425.html">In Verant's attempt to make Necros more GROUP FRIENDLY, they disabled Summon Corpse!</a></B><P>

That's right, Summon Corpse doesn't WORK in Velious!<P>

<B>Well… no.<P>

There will be some places where summon corpse is restricted in its use, and perhaps others where it won't work at all. But, for the most part it works just fine in Velious.<P>

I'm sorry, I was a bit misleading in my response (actually, I was wrong). Summon corpse will work in every zone in Velious. But in some places it will be limited in its use. This limited use will mean, in most cases, that you can only summon corpses to the zone-in location.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037426.html">Oopsie on the Velious Box?</a></B><P>

Ok so the minimum requirements are....<BR>
200 Pentium<BR>
64 MB ram<BR>
16 MB video card<BR>

and the recommended configuration is....<P>

350 Pentium<BR>
128 MB ram<BR>
8 mb video card. <P>

<B>Yes, we noticed that too... a bit too late. If you switch those too RAM numbers it's correct...<P>

:)<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037429.html">Velious Bugs and broken additions - post yours here.</a></B><P>

Hey, just for fun, everyone who finds a bug in velios post it here. It will be like the content contest turbine is running, except it focuses more on what verant is best at.<P>

<B>Fair enough. Despite the obviously sarcastic intent of your post, let's use this space to discuss bugs that you find in Velious. I'll pass them on to the team.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Marnes wrote: "All inspections of items and spell effects overlap the inventory screen (if near middle) making the overlapping areas terrible, if not impossible to read."<P>

<B>Are you using 640x480 resolution? Rowyl is also looking into this, but a higher resolution helps this a lot.</B><P>

"In addition, the typical translucent backdrop for the inventory screen makes it difficult to read. I'm thinking something that large may as well be opaque. Making it transparent or translucent makes it difficult to see anyways in most situations."<P>

<B>I'll make Rowyl aware of this. I think he's already got something in mind for this. But, personally, I can read it just fine.</B><P>

"The boxes in the inventory screen are difficult to identify.. would be nice to see labels in the slots. This is a problem with "auto equipping" the range weapon and it goes into the primary slot after looting corpse. 
One nice thing is that you can move the inventory window very close to the loot screen and click stuff on the "auto equip" box without having to move your cursor very far."<P>

<B>I talked to Rowyl about this, and he's already got a plan for that too… </B><P>

"Right clicking on my /assist social in full screen mode blanks the chat area forcing me to edit the social in console mode... probably the case with any social. This actually started last night... after patch. 
After installing Velious, right clicking on my spell icons failed to bring up the description for it... after playing around, it just started working.... perhaps after bringing up the inventory screen for the first time.. forget."<P>

<B>We just fixed it so that right clicking would work properly. I'm not sure about the socials thing, except that you're probably right, that it has to go into console mode.<P>

I'll clue Rowyl in on this thread and let him read up on these things himself.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B>Ok, I have much better information on two of your questions (the fix is already there… so it's not broken).</B><P>

"All inspections of items and spell effects overlap the inventory screen (if near middle) making the overlapping areas terrible, if not impossible to read."<P>

<B>You can edit the eqclient.ini to manually move where this window pops up. The trick here is, your mouse is in use to open the window, so you can't really use it to move the window. So you have to move it by editing the ini file.</B><P>

"In addition, the typical translucent backdrop for the inventory screen makes it difficult to read."<P>

<B>/wincolor allows you to change the color of your background. This should make things more readable. You can type /wincolor and hit enter and you should get some parameters for the function.</B><P>

Cari wrote: "Shouldn't this kind of stuff have been taken care of oh say maybe.... before you release an expansion people have to pay money for?"<P>

<B>Well, most of the items he listed aren't really bugs. For example, the fact that it drops into console mode to edit socials isn't a bug, really. That's the way it's always worked. But that doesn't mean that we won't continue to make improvements on this stuff as we go.<P>

Alan</B>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="3">News bits from lead programmer Rowyl</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
