				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036457.html">a stealth fix, i think</a></B><P>

Not sure exactly when the fix happened, but it used to be that if you had every slot in your inventory full, but a less-than-full stack of something, if you tried to right-click loot another thing to go in that stack, you got the "inventory full" message. (ok, that was really convluted, but i'm tired). This was listed as a known bug with low priority for a fix. Looks like it finally got its day. Thanks.<P>

<B>Actually, that particular stealth fix (the full inventory with stackable thing) was done by that sneaky gnome Wamtin! <P>

-Rowyl</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036965.html">Disarm traps: ranger needed skill.</a></B><P>

Being a ranger, I would think that it is a rangers duty to know the lands and protect the people in the group of the dangers there.
Tracking helps, but VI gave that skill to away. Why don't we get disarm traps? Bard and rogues get it. I would think that a ranger could disarm a snag, bear trap, or any type of hinderance.<P>

<B>Eonfluff,<P>

I posted at least twice (once to a thread I KNOW you read) that the tracking enhancements would not be in Velious, and that they would come AFTER Velious.<P>

I find in interesting that you really hate that anyone other then Rangers got tracking, yet you feel that you should get an ability that only Rogues and Bards have... <P>

-Rowyl</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037407.html">Rowyl Please....</a></B><P>

Make it an option to turn off Transperent polygons for everything EXCEPT the text box...
And while you are at it make the text box less transperant. I'm sure many would like this...but make it an option...<P>

<B>If you have Velious, then you can do this already. The new /wincolor command will do that. You can control the color and translucency of each window.<P>

-Rowyl</B>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
