<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum8/HTML/002111.html">Cultural tailoring imbalance issues</a></B><P>

It's great that the Vale leathers are finally working, and that they take an imbue *however*, once the still-broken (as of last night) oak bark tannin is fixed for the wood elves, there are still some serious questions about ... yep ... that dreaded word ... balance ... between the two race's tailoring.<P>

<B>The misty acorns should be capable of being foraged. It sounds like when Hobart redid the forage tables he accidentaly added the oak bark to both zones. We'll have to wait for an all zone patch to fix the table but in the meantime I can add more acorn spawns.</B>
