				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="5">EverQuest Producer Letter updated</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[12/5/2000-3:24:07 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=292735"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[0]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><P>
Gordon Wrinn just dropped us an email to let us know the <a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/news/letter.shtml">Producer Letter was just updated</a> for the Scars of Velious launch. Jeff Butler talks about the new challenges and features the expansion offers, and goes over some of the development process in this write up. A very interesting and worthwhile read, here's a snip.
<Blockquote>
It seems that just a short while ago that I had the pleasure of announcing the launch of the first EverQuest expansion. Our desire to surpass the success of The Ruins of Kunark spurred us to set ambitious goals for The Scars of Velious. As the months of development passed the team overcame what seemed at the onset to be a daunting series of challenges, not the least of which included a tight schedule. We are humbly pleased to present The Scars of Velious without compromise or concession, and we hope that it meets and exceeds your expectations for value and quality in an EverQuest product
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="6">Official Scars of Velious site launches!</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[12/5/2000-3:23:07 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=292720"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[0]</font></a>
