				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037325.html">Quests and Inventory Slots</a></B><P>

<I>Something to keep in mind. Some quests will give you an item that requires a whole inventory slot (one of your main slots). If you do not have an open slot the item will fall to the ground. We all know that items that fall to the ground are not secure, and are not subject to reimbursement. So PLEASE make certain that you have an open inventory slot (at least one) when attempting quests.<P>

Alan</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037305.html">BUG: GUI and Alt-M problems</a></B><P>

This is a bug that deals with the new UI window that contains the Socials and Abilities button, etc.
Hitting Alt-M hides the Socials window but the window still intercepts all mouse clicks.<P>

<B>We've got that one fixed. It should be fixed with the patch on Thursday.<P>

Alan</B><P>

