				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="15">Luclin: The Stryngs of Ayre Tournament</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:ziyadah420@hotmail.com">Flarestar Bladesinger</b></a>
				[12/5/2000-1:57:05 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=292097"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[0]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
The Stryngs of Ayre will be hosting a non-profit, player run tournament for these four classes. These are meant to be contests of skill, and nothing but. As such, the rules are going to be a bit different. Any characters who are between level 25 and 39 are invited. The fee is 30pp per character, with the winner of each bracket taking the prize. Combatants will be chosen within a specific level range of each other, with no combatant being more than four levels above another to ensure a fair fight as well as is possible and still be able to hold the contest. ;)<P>

Here's the catch. As these are contests of skill, no special gear is allowed. That means for all three classes, come equipped in leather armor. It's cheap, requires no special effort to get, and gives no stat bonuses to give either combatant an advantage. Weapons are to be basic, meaning fine steel weapons only. No jewelry, again to keep from giving an advantage. Anyone caught breaking these rules will be disqualified.<P>

Rogues are allowed to use any poisons they choose, except for those causing effects similar to those listed below. Rangers are allowed the use of all magic except for the types prohibited below. Bards are to be allowed their choice between using weapons and instruments. However, should they choose instruments, they will be store-bought, not magical. All classes are to be allowed ranged weapons of their choice, provided they are store-bought.<P>

Hide/sneak, invisibility, etc. IS allowed. The only tactics disallowed are fear and charm. Stunning and mesmerization are allowable. All combatants are to remain on the raised platform at all times. If you move off of the platform, you will be disqualified.<P>

Spectators who wish to attend are welcome, of course. All we ask is that you keep off of the platform, refrain from excessive talking and casting during combat due to lag reasons. No outside buffs will be permitted, only those the combatants themselves are capable of. Combatants themselves will have to decide whether it's worth taking the risk their opponent won't attack while they are buffing themselves.<P>

Matches will be alternated between classes for each tier, meaning that the rogue 25-29 tier will fight, then rangers, then bards. After each tier is finished, the winners of each class may face each other in combat, provided all three agree to it. If they choose to do so, they will each do a /random 100, and the two highest fight first. The winner of that fight faces the third. Winner of that fight takes the entire pot for all three classes of that tier.<P>

Fights will continue as long as there are people who want to fight. Combatants will pay their entry fee as their tier and class begins combat. Basically, when the 25-29 tier of rogues is called, anyone who wishes to enter into that tier pays then. Once the tier has started, of course, no more entrants will be allowed. That should help to keep people from having to sit around for ages waiting. ;)<P>

Hopefully I'll have a Guide on-hand to assist. If not, then we'll just do the best we can. :) If anyone wants any clarification on the rules, please feel free to email me at <a href="mailto:ziyadah420@hotmail.com">ziyadah420@hotmail.com</a>. I hope to see all of you there.
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		

